<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN242-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. ollaiyūr kiḻāṉmakaṉ peruñcāttaṉaik kuṭavāyiṉallātaṉār (kuṭavāyiṟkīrattaṉār) pāṭiyatu.
        ituvumatu – 
        <app>
        <lem wit="#C2 #C3">ollaiyūr</lem>
        <rdg wit="#C8">ollaiyūrk</rdg>
        </app> 
        <app>
        <lem wit="#C2 #C3">kiḻārmaka<space quantity="12" unit="character"/></lem>
        <rdg wit="#C8">kiḻāṉmakaṉ peruñcāttaṉaik kuṭavāyi</rdg>
        </app> ṉallātaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN242">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>iḷaiyōr cūṭār vaḷaiyōr koyyār</l>
<l>nalliyāḻ maruppiṉ mella vāṅkip</l>
<l>pāṇaṉ cūṭāṉ pāṭiṉi yaṇiyā</l>
<l>ḷāṇmai tōṉṟa vāṭavark kaṭanta</l>
<l>valvēṟ cāttaṉ māynta piṉṟai</l>
<l>mullaiyum pūttiyō vollaiyūr nāṭṭē</l></lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">The young men won’t wear [it]. Those with bangles won’t pluck [it]. </l>
<l corresp="2">Not bending [it] softly around the neck of [his] good lute </l>
<l corresp="3">the bard won’t wear [it]. Songstresses won’t adorn themselves [with it]. </l>
<l corresp="5">After Cāttaṉ with a strong spear disappeared </l>
<l corresp="4">who overcame men so that [his] manliness appeared </l>
<l corresp="6">jasmine, would you flower, in the land of Ollaiyūr? </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
